content: Now looking at our partnerships for the XmAb bispecific Fc demand in our T-cell engager toolkit, last quarter, we highlighted encouraging early clinical data from Amgen’s AMG 509 program in prostate cancer, which, in addition to being an XmAb bispecific, uses the XmAb 2+1 multi-valent format for T cell engagement.
